    "url": "automation-flow.html",
    "title": "Automation Flow",
    "content": "Automation Flow  Wapi documentation Top Purchase Support Frontend Admin A A A Wapi documentation Automation Automation Builder Close Introduction Prerequisite Wapi Installation Overview Frontend Installation Backend Installation Local Server Live Server Database Seed Deployment Cpanel Virtual Private Server Vercel Core Features Advanced Features Usage Admin Usage Tenant Usage Agent Usage Admin Guide Dashboard Payment Transactions Users Short Links Subscription Manage Plans Subscriber Plans Manage Users All Users Add User Content Management Manage FAQs Manage Testimonials Pages Roles  Permissions Manage Landing Templates Library System Settings Payment Gateways Settings AI Models Languages Currencies Taxes Contact Inquiries Frontend Guide Dashboard WA Chat Chat Appearance Integrations Integrate WABA WABA Phone Numbers Templates Tools Tags Media Teams Agents Automations Automation Builder Predefined Actions Response Resources Keyword Trigger AI Call Assistant WhatsApp Form My Subscription Subscriptions Marketing Campaigns Orders Catalogues Webhooks Contacts Columns Import Jobs AI Config Developer Menu Automation Automation Builder 1 Overview Automation Flows are the core of your WhatsApp strategy Using a visual draganddrop interface you can build complex customer journeys that respond instantly to triggers reducing manual effort and maximizing customer engagement Efficiency Fact Automated flows can handle up to 90 of routine customer inquiries  freeing your agents for highvalue tasks 2 Automation Builder Interface The visual builder allows you to drag nodes from a library and connect them to create logicbased conversation paths Key Builder Components Canvas The workspace where you arrange and connect your nodes Trigger Nodes Define how the flow starts Keyword Event or API Action Nodes Send messages images or interactive buttons Logic Nodes Add conditions IfElse or delays to the flow 3 Implementation Workflow Follow these steps to build and activate your first automated workflow Step 1 Initiate Flow Navigate to Automation Flows from the sidebar Click on  Create New Flow  Enter a descriptive Flow Name eg Welcome Bot Step 2 Build Logic Drag a Keyword Trigger node onto the canvas Configure the keywords that should trigger this flow eg Hello Help Connect the trigger to a Message node Step 3 Save  Activate Validate your connections ensure every node has a path Click Save Flow at the top right Toggle the Status to Active to go live Example PostPurchase Engagement A common scenario for ecommerce brands Trigger Order Status updated to Delivered Action Send a How did we do message with review buttons Logic If Positive  Send coupon If Negative  Notify agent 4 Governance  Best Practices Logic Optimization Default Fallbacks Always include a path for when conditions arent met Human Handover Ensure one path leads to a live agent for complex issues Testing Test keywords from multiple sandbox accounts before release Note Flows with high dropoff rates often have too many steps Keep your conversational paths concise and valuable Copyright 2026  WAPI  WhatsApp Marketing Platform by PixelStrap"
