    "url": "billing-plans.html",
    "title": "Subscription Management",
    "content": "Subscription Management  Wapi documentation Top Purchase Support Frontend Admin A A A Wapi documentation Subscription Management Close Introduction Prerequisite Wapi Installation Overview Frontend Installation Backend Installation Local Server Live Server Database Seed Deployment Cpanel Virtual Private Server Vercel Core Features Advanced Features Usage Admin Usage Tenant Usage Agent Usage Admin Guide Dashboard Payment Transactions Users Short Links Subscription Manage Plans Subscriber Plans Manage Users All Users Add User Content Management Manage FAQs Manage Testimonials Pages Roles  Permissions Manage Landing Templates Library System Settings Payment Gateways Settings AI Models Languages Currencies Taxes Contact Inquiries Frontend Guide Dashboard WA Chat Chat Appearance Integrations Integrate WABA WABA Phone Numbers Templates Tools Tags Media Teams Agents Automations Automation Builder Predefined Actions Response Resources Keyword Trigger AI Call Assistant WhatsApp Form My Subscription Subscriptions Marketing Campaigns Orders Catalogues Webhooks Contacts Columns Import Jobs AI Config Developer Menu Subscription Management 1 Overview The Subscription Management feature is the central hub for managing your Wapi platform plan billing details and service limits It provides realtime visibility into feature consumption ensuring you remain within your operational capacity while offering flexible paths for scaling your business communication infrastructure Centralized Control Manage plans billing cycles and payment methods in one unified interface Realtime Tracking Monitor usage limits for contacts campaigns and AI agents with live progress bars Flexible Scaling Upgrade or downgrade ties instantly to align with your business growth 2 Dashboard Infrastructure The dashboard is segmented into highimpact cards designed for immediate operational clarity Current Plan Details Displays your active service tier and lifecycle status Plan Name Your current tier identifier eg Plan 1 Status Indicators for Active Expired or Canceled status Renewal Date The exact date for the next automated billing cycle Usage Analytics Operational Vectors Granular tracking of 12 feature consumption metrics Quantified Metrics Contacts Total unique users in your CRM Bots Count of Template and Message bots deployed Campaigns Total active marketing broadcasts Staff Members Authorized agent seats Conversations Monthly message thread count Assets Bot Flows Broadcasts and Canned Replies Unlimited Features REST API Access Webhook Support Priority Support Channels 3 Billing  Lifecycle Protocol Financial Records Monitor how your account is funded and billed Payment Type Origin of subscription eg Admin Generated  Manual Amount Paid Total dollar value of the current cycle Billing Type Cycle frequency eg Onetime  Monthly Next Billing Cycle Realtime countdown to the next charge date Plan Modification Workflow Access the Manage Plan modal to synchronize capacity with demand UPGRADE Instantly scale limits and unlock enterprise features DOWNGRADE Optimize costs by moving to a lighter service tier CANCEL Terminate recurring billing and lock feature access 4 Strategic Governance Usage buffer Monitor Usage Analytics weekly upgrade when reaching 85 capacity to prevent service interruption Limit Hierarchy Note that downgrading may restrict access to complex features like Bot Flows or Webhooks  Renewal Clarity Billing is transparent the Next Billing Cycle card always reflects the upcoming commitment date Troubleshooting If features are inaccessible verify the Status in the Current Plan card is set to Active and credit balance is sufficient Copyright 2026  WAPI  WhatsApp Marketing Platform by PixelStrap"
