    "url": "update.html",
    "title": "Introduction",
    "content": "Introduction  Wapi documentation Top Purchase Support Frontend Admin A A A Wapi documentation Chat collaborate and create teams effortlessly with Wapi Close Introduction Prerequisite Wapi Installation Overview Frontend Installation Backend Installation Local Server Live Server Database Seed Deployment Cpanel Virtual Private Server Vercel Core Features Advanced Features Usage Admin Usage Tenant Usage Agent Usage Admin Guide Dashboard Payment Transactions Users Short Links Subscription Manage Plans Subscriber Plans Manage Users All Users Add User Content Management Manage FAQs Manage Testimonials Pages Roles  Permissions Manage Landing Templates Library System Settings Payment Gateways Settings AI Models Languages Currencies Taxes Contact Inquiries Frontend Guide Dashboard WA Chat Chat Appearance Integrations Integrate WABA WABA Phone Numbers Templates Tools Tags Media Teams Agents Automations Automation Builder Predefined Actions Response Resources Keyword Trigger AI Call Assistant WhatsApp Form My Subscription Subscriptions Marketing Campaigns Orders Catalogues Webhooks Contacts Columns Import Jobs AI Config Developer Menu Welcome to Wapi  How to maintain future Updates with Old Version If you want which file changes are on the latest updated version then you have to manage the git repository by yourself You can give same name as we have given wapiadmin or give your name like demoTest For Example we have create project with name demoTest Note  Before proceeding ensure you create a backup as we are not responsible for any potential loss Please ensure you follow the same steps separately for each of the three folders wapiapi wapifrontend and wapiadmin Do not directly change in your real project it will show errors Regards package name version and etc Follow below steps on how to update existing source code Download Github Desktop from url as per your system like MacOs or Windows httpsdesktopgithubcom Now Login in Github Desktop and configure the setup with your github You have already create your project in Visual Studio Open Github Desktop on left hand panel top click on One side menu open in that click on Add button On click add button dropdown menu will open in that click on Create New Repository After click create new repository one popup will appear in the form add your project name your project path where it is located and click on Create repository button After above process you can check in your project there is another folder created with same project name just remove that folder After above process complete click on Publish repository  one confirmation popup will appear in that again click on Publish repository button Now download project your project Codecanyon unzip the folder click on wapiadmin folder now copy all the files and paste it in your project Now Again go to Github Desktop give comment and click on commint on main button Now click on Push origin Click right click on your project name from list and click on View on Github  For check open github in google chrome login in your git and check Now click on Changes for check total number for file changes and which files has been changed Now click on Changes for check total number for file changes and which files has been changed You can see total number of changes and which file has been changed Every time when ever new update came in project do same process download code unzip folder and paste in your dumy project and push it and go to github and click on changes you can see the in all the files where ever changes happens Copy the changes one by one and paste it your real project Quick Access Lets get started  your teams new home is wapi Chat Introduction Overview and background information Prerequisite Required tools and setup Wapi Installation Setup guide and configuration Copyright 2026  WAPI  WhatsApp Marketing Platform by PixelStrap"
